From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Akanksha Hotta <akanksha.hotta@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 09:00:45 +0530
Subject: Add a callback to determine attribute visibility
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implement compatibility layer for configfs_group_operations.is_visible
member introduced in upstream v6.12kernels to allow dynamic visibility
control of configfs attributes. This uses this for controlling
visibility of device and SR-IOV configuration groups based on device
capabilities.

So implemeted and conditional probe if is_visible member availability via
struct then include member assignment only when supported but member isn't
assigned on old kernels which holds original implementation.

Reference:
   0e6a35b93745bb
   fs/configfs: Add a callback to determine attribute visibility

Signed-off-by: Akanksha Hotta <akanksha.hotta@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_configfs.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_configfs.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_configfs.c
index 7fd07d1..a1e1a8c 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_configfs.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_configfs.c
@@ -853,7 +853,9 @@ static bool xe_config_device_is_visible(struct config_item *item,
 }
 
 static struct configfs_group_operations xe_config_device_group_ops = {
+#ifndef BPM_CONFIGFS_GROUP_OPS_IS_VISIBLE_NOT_PRESENT
 	.is_visible	= xe_config_device_is_visible,
+#endif
 };
 
 static const struct config_item_type xe_config_device_type = {
@@ -916,7 +918,9 @@ static bool xe_config_sriov_is_visible(struct config_item *item,
 }
 
 static struct configfs_group_operations xe_config_sriov_group_ops = {
+#ifndef BPM_CONFIGFS_GROUP_OPS_IS_VISIBLE_NOT_PRESENT
 	.is_visible	= xe_config_sriov_is_visible,
+#endif
 };
 
 static const struct config_item_type xe_config_sriov_type = {
-- 
